  "prompt": "When a parking sign says 2-hour parking from 8 to 5 on Monday-Friday, what does it mean for the remainder of the time?",
  "response": "When a parking sign specifies \"2-hour parking from 8 to 5 on Monday-Friday,\" it means that during those hours on weekdays, you are allowed to park for a maximum of 2 hours. Outside of those hours (before 8 AM and after 5 PM on weekdays and all day on weekends), the restriction does not apply, which generally means you can park there for longer periods without worrying about the 2-hour limitation. However, it's important to ensure that there are no other signs or local regulations that impose different restrictions during the remainder of the time.",
